Currently, a Slack channel has to have a subscription to a JIRA board in order to use  "/JIRA ISSUEKEY-123". I love using this functionality to check in on tasks quickly, but I don't need a channel notification every time something is updated in that board. 
 
There should be a way to mute notifications on a subscription so that the "/JIRA ISSUEKEY-123" feature could be used without getting notifications of task updates. Having 10 people in one board makes for a LOT of notifications. 
 
On the flip side of that, being able to choose who you see notifications from would be helpful and limit the number of updates in a channel.

