There is a nice feature in JIRA that allows users to hide menus in their Agile boards. However, this does not persist and there is no way to tell JIRA that you'd like to hide the menus when you first navigate to the board.

A use case for this that I'm dealing with is:

I want to embed our board in a Microsoft Teams tab, but I don't want all the menus. I would rather it simply hid the menus similar to what the "Hide Menus" menu option does when you are viewing a board.

By the way, the screenshots are from someone else's repository. I have no idea who they are or what was in their repo. An example of the URL change would be something like:


{code:java}
https://jira.atlassian.com/secure/RapidBoard.jspa?rapidView=426&hideMenus{code}

